#COVID19 #Algorithms #YNH #Humans #Privacy Google Flu Trends is already capable of ringing the flu alarm bells ten days before traditional health services. A more ambitious project is called the Google Baseline Study.

#COVID19 #Algorithms #YNH #Humans In 2008 Google actually launched Google Flu Trends  that tracks flu outbreaks by monitoring Google searches. The service is still being developed & due to #Privacy limitations it tracks only search words & allegedly avoids reading private emails

#COVID19 #Algorithms #YNH #Humans If Angelina Jolie was willing to sacrifice her #Privacy in order to raise awareness of breast cancer  why shouldn’t Mary make a similar sacrifice in order to fight epidemics? This isn’t a theoretical idea.
#COVID19 #Algorithms #YNH #Humans #Privacy However  for Google to work its magic  Mary must allow Google not only to read her messages  but also to share the information with the health authorities.

#COVID19 #Algorithms #YNH #Humans #Privacy On the very first morning Mary woke up feeling a bit unwell  and before going to work she emailed a colleague  ‘I have a headache  but I’ll be there.’ That’s all Google needs.

#COVID19 #YNH #Humans #Privacy Suppose on an average day words ‘headache’  ‘fever’  ‘nausea’ & ‘sneezing’ appear 100 000 times in London emails & searches If today #Algorithms notice they appear 300 000 times  then bingo! Flu epidemic No need to wait till Mary goes to her doctor

#COVID19 #Algorithms #YNH #Humans #Privacy All Google needs to do is monitor the words Londoners type in their emails and in Google’s search engine  and cross-reference them with a database of disease symptoms.

#COVID19 #Algorithms #YNH #Humans #Privacy Somebody up in NHS headquarters hopefully analyses this data together with reports streaming in from thousands of other doctors  concluding that flu is on the march. All this takes a lot of time. Google could do it in minutes.

#COVID19 #Algorithms #YNH #Humans #Privacy When things don’t improve  Mary makes an appointment with the doctor  goes to the clinic and describes the symptoms. The doctor types the data into the computer

#COVID19 #Algorithms #YNH #Humans #Privacy When Mary wakes up one morning feeling a bit under the weather  she doesn’t run straight to her doctor. She waits a few hours  or even a day or two  hoping that a nice cup of tea with honey will do the trick.
